page.title: 04Forests in Woodlands
page.content: Our community is called Woodlands of Durris because of the huge amount of trees around.Quite a bit of the block is covered in woods.Most of them are conifers.A lot of these are being cut down and replaced by oak or more conifers.The oak plants are enclosed by a yellow tube to protect them from rabbits.The conifers are mostly Sitka Spruce,Scots pine,and Larch.The forests were mainly planted deliberately by the Forestry Commission.Down in Woodlands Park,an old estate,there are mostly Rhododendron bushes,as well as deciduous trees like Silver Birch,Beech,Oak,Ash,Rowan and Horse Chestnut.There are also evergreens like Sequoia,Cypress,Cedar,Pine and Holly. Woodlands Park is well known for the variety of trees that grow there.
